paid her for the past week and kissed her hand, light as a faded leaf.

As he walked back down the passage he remembered that today the dancers had invited him to a party and he decided not to go away just yet; he could always take a room in a hotel, even after midnight if necessary.

“And tomorrow Mary arrives,” he exclaimed mentally, glancing round the ceiling, floor and walls with a blissful and frightened look. “And tomorrow I’m going to take her away,” he reflected with the same i